  <p class="text-xs text-text-muted -mt-4 mb-8">
    Legend: green check means it is there and typed, amber bar means partial or sold separately,
    red cross means it is not part of the tool.
  </p>

  <h2>What you don't have to write anymore</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Hand-written row interfaces that drift away from the schema.</li>
    <li>Generic gymnastics to carry a query's shape into a component.</li>
    <li>Manual casts when you fetch a related record.</li>
    <li>Documentation comments that promise a shape the code no longer matches.</li>
    <li>That one bug that only shows up when a field gets renamed in production.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Where we are today, honestly</h2>
  <p>
    Reads, updates, and backend calls are fully typed today. Create payloads still accept a
    slightly looser shape than the rest of the API, and tightening that is on the roadmap. We
    will update this page as it lands.
  </p>
</FeaturePage>
